COPS are looking for a suspect believed to have been involved in the gang rape of a woman on 1 July. The Krugersdorp policeâ€™s family violence, child protection and sexual offences unit has released an identikit of the suspect. The victim (31) was walking towards the taxi rank along Von Brandis Street in Krugersdorp when she was accosted by three suspects and one of them, who was speaking Sotho, grabbed her by her jersey and took her to the bushes where she was gang raped without condoms. She later reported the matter to the police and was able to identify one of the suspects through an identification kit. The suspect is said to be a Sotho-speaking man, between 30 and 40 years old, 1,65m, medium build and coffee colour in complexion. He was wearing black trousers, a blue reflector and black bennie. Anyone who might have information that could lead to the arrest of this suspect may contact the Krugersdorp police on 011 951 1151 or contact the CrimeStop number on 08600 10111 or information may be communicated via MySAPS App or SMS number 32211 and remain anonymous or may contact investigating officer Constable Phillip Lenyai on 073 915 3918 or office landline 011 951 1729.